    "created_at": "2014-07-04T15:31:39Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-07-04T15:31:39Z",
    "body": "It is important for some application to get the real working directory, for example in atom/atom the `atom` command needs to know current working directory to open the file passed in command parameters.\n\nIf you want to keep the exact behavior with node-webkit, you can just do `process.chdir(__dirname)` as you have already figured out.\n"
